WEBVTT

00:02.132 --> 00:05.179
[ DOG BARKING IN DISTANCE ]

00:08.878 --> 00:11.663
[ FAN WHIRRING ]

00:11.707 --> 00:17.756
[ WATER RUNNING ]

00:17.800 --> 00:20.194
[ WATER CONTINUES ]

00:25.851 --> 00:27.114
[ TURNS WATER OFF ]

00:59.233 --> 01:00.886
[ TURNS FAN OFF ]

01:03.019 --> 01:04.716
[ FAN WINDS DOWN ]

01:29.915 --> 01:31.265
[ DOOR OPENS ]

01:47.455 --> 01:50.022
CLEAR.

02:09.433 --> 02:11.870
[ DOOR OPENS ]

02:11.914 --> 02:15.178
[ GUNSHOTS ]

02:15.222 --> 02:17.354
[ BUZZER ] Man over P.A.: STAND DOWN.
EXERCISE COMPLETE.

02:17.398 --> 02:19.617
DAMN. WE'LL GET YOU GUYS
NEXT TIME.

02:19.661 --> 02:20.923
WE WON?

02:20.966 --> 02:24.013
[ APPLAUSE ]

02:28.974 --> 02:30.976
[ SIGHS ]

02:31.020 --> 02:32.891
F.B.I.'s HAVING
A GOOD SHOWING THIS YEAR.

02:32.935 --> 02:34.850
THANK YOU.

02:34.893 --> 02:37.026
COLONEL?YES?

02:38.332 --> 02:41.073
I BELIEVE YOU HAVE
SOMETHING FOR ME.

02:48.820 --> 02:50.996
WEEK'S NOT OVER YET.

02:51.040 --> 02:52.346
BRING IT ON.

02:54.739 --> 02:56.654
[ SIGHS ]

03:05.315 --> 03:07.622
THIS IDEA YOU HAVE
ABOUT QUITTING,

03:07.665 --> 03:09.145
WERE YOU EVER GONNA
BRING IT UP AGAIN?

03:09.189 --> 03:11.321
WELL, IT'S JUST A THOUGHT.

03:11.365 --> 03:13.367
FOR THE RECORD,
I ENJOY WHAT WE DO.

03:13.410 --> 03:14.846
WELL, YOU MIGHT ENJOY PARIS

03:14.890 --> 03:16.892
OR LEARNING
PEDAL STEEL GUITAR.

03:16.935 --> 03:18.546
PEDAL STEEL GUITAR?

03:18.589 --> 03:22.071
THE WORLD IS INFINITE
IN ITS POSSIBILITIES.

03:22.114 --> 03:24.856
IT'S NOT GONNA BE AS EASY
TO WALK AWAY AS YOU THINK.

03:24.900 --> 03:26.771
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT?

03:26.815 --> 03:29.687
YOU ENJOY THE MENTAL STIMULATION
FAR MORE THAN YOU LET ON.

03:29.731 --> 03:31.341
AGENT LISBON.

03:31.385 --> 03:32.821
COLONEL RAYMOND.

03:32.864 --> 03:36.955
WE MET AT A SEMINAR --

03:36.999 --> 03:38.566
UH, COLONEL RAYMOND,
THIS IS PATRICK JANE.

03:38.609 --> 03:41.482
HE WORKS AS A CONSULTANT
WITH THE TEAM.

03:41.525 --> 03:44.267
THAT WAS SOME FINE WORK
BACK THERE

03:44.311 --> 03:45.964
CLEARING THOSE ROOMS
JUST NOW.

03:46.008 --> 03:47.662
IF YOU EVER DECIDE YOU'RE
TIRED OF THE BUREAU,

03:47.705 --> 03:49.316
I CAN HAVE A SPACE
FOR YOU.

03:49.359 --> 03:51.753
THAT'S FLATTERING.
THANK YOU.

03:51.796 --> 03:54.843
NOW IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME,

03:54.886 --> 03:55.757
[ CHUCKLES ] YEAH.

04:02.198 --> 04:04.896
DID -- DID YOU EVER HAVE
A FLING WITH THAT GUY?

04:04.940 --> 04:06.289
WHAT?

04:06.333 --> 04:08.422
OF COURSE NOT. SORRY.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.293
IT'S JUST STRANGE.

04:10.337 --> 04:13.296
STRANGE THAT I DIDN'T HAVE
A FLING WITH COLONEL RAYMOND?

04:13.340 --> 04:15.994
YEAH, THERE'S SOMETHING
GOING ON THERE.

04:17.431 --> 04:19.171
YOU DON'T KNOW?

04:19.215 --> 04:20.782
KNOW WHAT?

04:20.825 --> 04:22.566
HIS WIFE WAS MURDERED
EIGHT MONTHS AGO.

04:22.610 --> 04:23.915
REALLY?

04:23.959 --> 04:26.614
IT WAS ALL OVER THE NEWS.

04:26.657 --> 04:28.485
DID THEY CATCH ANYONE?

04:28.529 --> 04:31.358
YEAH, THEY ARRESTED SOMEBODY
RIGHT AFTER.

04:31.401 --> 04:32.794
I NEED A SHOWER.

04:32.837 --> 04:35.623
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:38.190 --> 04:40.671
EIGHT MONTHS AGO, HUH?

04:48.984 --> 04:59.690
♪♪♪

04:59.734 --> 05:02.432
THE MURDER OF COLONEL RAYMOND'S
WIFE IS CLOSED.

05:03.999 --> 05:05.392
HMM.

05:05.435 --> 05:07.568
SO YOU'RE NOT INTERESTED
IN HEARING MY THEORY?

05:11.136 --> 05:13.661
OKAY. WHAT'S YOUR THEORY?

05:13.704 --> 05:15.140
WELL, I DON'T HAVE ONE YET,

05:15.184 --> 05:17.317
BUT THAT'S WHY WE NEED
TO LOOK INTO IT.

05:17.360 --> 05:18.535
EXCUSE ME. SORRY.

05:18.579 --> 05:20.276
CHO NEEDS YOU TO SIGN THIS.

05:20.320 --> 05:22.191
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

05:22.234 --> 05:23.714
SO YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING?

05:23.758 --> 05:25.629
NO. AT THIS POINT,
I'M JUST CURIOUS.

05:25.673 --> 05:27.544
CURIOSITY KILLED THE CAT.

05:32.506 --> 05:34.551
ALSO CURED POLIO.

05:34.595 --> 05:38.033
AARON RAYMOND IS NOT JUST
A COLONEL IN THE MARINES.

05:38.076 --> 05:40.035
HE'S A DECORATED WAR HERO.

05:40.078 --> 05:42.429
AND THEY'VE ALREADY ARRESTED
A MAN FOR THE MURDER.

05:42.472 --> 05:45.388
SO WHAT MAKES YOU THINK THAT MAN
DIDN'T COMMIT THE CRIME?

05:45.432 --> 05:46.955
WELL, I'M NOT SURE
THAT HE DIDN'T.

05:46.998 --> 05:48.391
I'M JUST SAYING,
THERE IS --

05:48.435 --> 05:52.221
THERE IS SOMETHING OFF ABOUT
THIS COLONEL RAYMOND.

05:52.264 --> 05:55.572
[ SIGHS ]

05:55.616 --> 05:57.400
LISBON, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

05:57.444 --> 05:59.837
IF JANE SAYS IT'S WORTH
LOOKING INTO,

05:59.881 --> 06:01.230
THEN IT'S WORTH
LOOKING INTO.

06:01.273 --> 06:02.579
YOU KNOW TO TRUST
HIS INSTINCTS.

06:04.929 --> 06:08.672
NO INTERROGATIONS, NO SEARCHES.

06:08.716 --> 06:11.458
IF YOU WANT TO TALK TO ANYONE,
USE A COVER STORY.

06:11.501 --> 06:14.374
A CIVIL RIGHTS CASE FOR THE MAN
WHO WAS ARRESTED MAYBE.

06:14.417 --> 06:18.247
RAYMOND IS NOT TO LEARN THAT
WE ARE LOOKING INTO THIS.

06:18.290 --> 06:21.206
ANYONE FINDS OUT
THAT WE'RE INVESTIGATING HERE,

06:21.250 --> 06:22.860
IT'S OVER.

06:24.384 --> 06:25.646
DEAL.

06:25.689 --> 06:27.256
DEAL.

06:29.693 --> 06:31.303
POUND IT.

06:31.347 --> 06:34.872
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:34.916 --> 06:36.483
THANK YOU, SIR.

06:47.407 --> 06:48.756
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

06:50.714 --> 06:52.368
YOU WANT A COFFEE
OR SOMETHING?

06:52.412 --> 06:53.587
I'M GOOD, THANKS.

06:53.630 --> 06:55.371
YEAH, IT SUCKS ANYWAY.

06:55.415 --> 06:58.418
I GOT TO TELL YOU,

06:58.461 --> 07:01.421
I'M NOT THRILLED TO HAVE
MY WORK CHECKED BY THE F.B.I.

07:01.464 --> 07:03.901
I'M NOT THRILLED TO BE HERE.

07:03.945 --> 07:05.947
MIND IF I ASK WHY?

07:05.990 --> 07:09.341
THE MAN YOU CHARGED
WITH THE CRIME,

07:09.385 --> 07:11.866
TO FILE A CIVIL RIGHTS VIOLATION
AGAINST YOUR DEPARTMENT.

07:11.909 --> 07:14.346
CIVIL RIGHTS VIOLATION?
FOR WHAT?

07:14.390 --> 07:15.739
YOU TELL ME.

07:15.783 --> 07:18.394
WE CAUGHT YOUR MAN JEFFERSON

07:18.438 --> 07:20.614
IN NICOLE RAYMOND'S CAR

07:20.657 --> 07:22.442
ONE DAY AFTER
SHE WAS MURDERED.

07:22.485 --> 07:25.053
THE VICTIM'S WALLET
WAS IN THE CAR,

07:25.096 --> 07:27.490
AS WELL AS JEWELRY
STOLEN FROM THE HOUSE.

07:27.534 --> 07:29.492
MURDER SCENE HAD SIGNS
OF A BREAK-IN.

07:29.536 --> 07:31.494
SLAM DUNK.

07:31.538 --> 07:34.236
YOU LOOK AT ANY OTHER SUSPECTS?
THE HUSBAND, MAYBE?

07:34.279 --> 07:36.630
YEAH, YEAH, 9 TIMES OUT OF 10,
HUSBAND DID IT.

07:36.673 --> 07:37.848
THIS IS TIME NUMBER 10.

07:37.892 --> 07:39.589
HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

07:39.633 --> 07:41.243
CHECK THIS OUT.

07:41.286 --> 07:43.245
AARON RAYMOND'S CAR WAS
IN THE SHOP THAT DAY.

07:43.288 --> 07:44.594
THEY TOOK NICOLE'S CAR.

07:44.638 --> 07:46.596
SHE DROPPED HIM OFF AT WORK.

07:46.640 --> 07:49.251
THEY GOT CAUGHT
IN A RED LIGHT CAMERA.

07:49.294 --> 07:51.993
M.E. SAYS BASED ON
LIVER TEMP,

07:52.036 --> 07:56.127
NICOLE RAYMOND WAS KILLED
NO EARLIER THAN 10:00 A.M.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.652
AARON RAYMOND GOT TO WORK
THAT DAY AT 9:00.

07:58.695 --> 08:00.697
WE GOT CONFIRMATION
HE NEVER LEFT.

08:03.221 --> 08:05.963
YOU WANNA TELL ME
HOWHE COULD BE THE KILLER?

08:11.621 --> 08:13.797
[ GATE DOOR CREAKS ]

08:17.888 --> 08:19.542
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?[ GATE LOCKS ]

08:19.586 --> 08:22.284
WE WANTED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT NICOLE RAYMOND'S DEATH.

08:22.327 --> 08:24.939
[ SCOFFS ] WHY?

08:24.982 --> 08:28.333
ZACH, THE F.B.I. ASSURES ME
THIS IS AN OFF-THE-RECORD CHAT.

08:28.377 --> 08:31.075
THEY JUST WANT TO HEAR
OUR SIDE.

08:31.119 --> 08:32.903
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
YEAH, RIGHT.

08:36.820 --> 08:38.256
WHY DON'T YOU TELL US
WHAT YOU WERE DOING

08:38.300 --> 08:40.781
BEFORE YOU WERE ARRESTED?

08:40.824 --> 08:43.610
I WAS LIVING IN A HALFWAY HOUSE.

08:43.653 --> 08:46.917
ALL RIGHT? BAGGING GROCERIES.
[ SIGHS ]

08:46.961 --> 08:50.573
THEN I MOVED IN WITH A FRIEND --
YOU KNOW, COUCH SURFING.

08:50.617 --> 08:52.183
HE GOT A NEW GIRLFRIEND,
SHE DIDN'T LIKE ME,

08:52.227 --> 08:53.707
SO I HAD TO MOVE OUT.

08:55.970 --> 08:56.971
YOU WERE HOMELESS.

08:58.581 --> 09:00.670
SHORT-TERM.

09:00.714 --> 09:02.933
I MEAN, YEAH, I COULD HAVE MOVED
BACK INTO THE HALFWAY HOUSE,

09:02.977 --> 09:06.067
BUT THEM PEOPLE
BE ON YOUR CASE, AND...

09:06.110 --> 09:08.504
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
THE DAY OF THE ARREST?

09:09.723 --> 09:11.507
[ SCOFFS ]

09:13.422 --> 09:15.598
LOOK, I FOUND THE CAR.
ALL RIGHT?

09:15.642 --> 09:17.382
KEYS IN IT AND EVERYTHING.

09:17.426 --> 09:20.211
IS IT REALLY STEALING IF SOMEONE
JUST LEAVES SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

09:23.780 --> 09:25.782
YOU'VE BEEN ARRESTED
THREE TIMES.

09:25.826 --> 09:27.175
SHOPLIFTING, POSSESSION.

09:27.218 --> 09:29.090
SO?

09:29.133 --> 09:30.482
IT'S NOT CRAZY TO THINK
YOU MIGHT TRY

09:30.526 --> 09:32.615
ROBBING SOMEBODY'S HOUSE.

09:32.659 --> 09:35.487
LET'S JUST CUT RIGHT TO IT.
DID YOU KILL NICOLE RAYMOND?

09:35.531 --> 09:38.926
[ SIGHS ]

09:38.969 --> 09:41.711
MAN, I NEVER KILLED ANYBODY.

09:49.501 --> 09:51.025
WHAT?

09:52.504 --> 09:54.594
WELL, WHAT DO YOU THINK?

09:54.637 --> 09:56.421
YOU BELIEVE HIM?

09:56.465 --> 09:57.901
AGENTS.

09:59.033 --> 10:01.818
IT LOOKS BAD, BUT ZACH
DIDN'T DO THIS.

10:01.862 --> 10:07.607
HE'S PROBABLY GONNA GET
THE NEEDLE.

10:07.650 --> 10:09.043
IF HE'S TELLING THE TRUTH,

10:09.086 --> 10:10.653
THEN RAYMOND KILLED HIS WIFE

10:10.697 --> 10:12.176
AND THEN DUMPED THE CAR
IN A BAD NEIGHBORHOOD

10:12.220 --> 10:13.961
JUST HOPING SOMEBODY
WOULD STEAL IT.

10:14.004 --> 10:16.833
WELL, THAT'S NOT OUTSIDE
THE REALM OF POSSIBILITY.

10:16.877 --> 10:19.357
EVERY GOOD PLAN NEEDS
A LITTLE BIT OF LUCK.

10:22.317 --> 10:24.101
WE SHOULD GO VISIT
THE CRIME SCENE.

10:34.895 --> 10:37.071
[ DIALING ]

10:38.289 --> 10:39.900
HI, JUDY.

10:39.943 --> 10:41.815
UH, MY GIRLFRIEND AND I
ARE OUT HOUSE HUNTING

10:41.858 --> 10:44.905
AND, UH, WE SAW A LOVELY
PLACE ON ROOSEVELT.

10:44.948 --> 10:47.081
WONDERING IF WE COULD TAKE
A LITTLE PEEK INSIDE.

10:48.082 --> 10:49.649
YEAH, WE'RE OUT FRONT.

10:49.692 --> 10:51.563
SEE YOU SOON. BYE.

10:53.391 --> 10:54.349
ON HER WAY.

10:54.392 --> 10:56.133
AH.

10:58.527 --> 10:59.963
OOH.

11:00.007 --> 11:02.096
AS YOU CAN SEE, THIS HOUSE
IS MOVE-IN READY.

11:02.139 --> 11:03.837
[ DOOR CLOSES, SWITCH CLICKS ]

11:03.880 --> 11:06.187
THERE'S A LOT TO LOVE
ABOUT THIS PLACE,

11:06.230 --> 11:09.190
BUT IF YOU ASK ME,
THIS COZY LIVING AREA

11:09.233 --> 11:10.800
IS A REAL DREAM.

11:10.844 --> 11:12.193
HOW LONG HAS IT BEEN
ON THE MARKET?

11:12.236 --> 11:13.716
UM, A COUPLE MONTHS.

11:13.760 --> 11:15.979
RALLY? AT THIS PRICE?
WHAT'S THE CATCH?

11:16.023 --> 11:19.200
[ LAUGHS ] WAIT UNTIL YOU
SEE THE MASTER BATH.

11:19.243 --> 11:20.767
IS THERE SOMETHING YOU'RE NOT
TELLING US, JUDY?

11:22.682 --> 11:24.509
OUT WITH IT.

11:24.553 --> 11:27.687
OH. UM... [ HUFFS ]

11:27.730 --> 11:30.298
WELL, UH, THERE WAS
A DEATH HERE.

11:30.341 --> 11:32.039
A MURDER.

11:32.082 --> 11:33.605
OOH.

11:33.649 --> 11:35.216
SHOULDN'T YOU HAVE TOLD US
THAT TO BEGIN WITH?

11:35.259 --> 11:37.740
ISN'T THERE A LAW
ABOUT THAT?YEAH.

11:37.784 --> 11:41.004
I-I DON'T KNOW IF IT'S
MY RESPONSIBILITY --

11:41.048 --> 11:42.745
UH, IF YOU DON'T MIND,
PRIVATELY.MM.

11:42.789 --> 11:44.747
OH. SURE. WELL, I HAVE
SOME CALLS TO MAKE,

11:44.791 --> 11:46.444
SO I'LL BE OUT IN MY CAR.

11:46.488 --> 11:47.619
JUST TAKE YOUR TIME.

11:52.146 --> 11:53.364
HMM.

11:53.408 --> 11:54.452
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

12:00.023 --> 12:02.809
UH, WINDOW WAS OPEN,
SCREEN OUTSIDE.

12:02.852 --> 12:05.637
THE COPS THINK THAT'S HOW
JEFFERSON BROKE INTO THE HOUSE.

12:05.681 --> 12:07.509
THROUGH HERE?UH-HUH.

12:07.552 --> 12:09.903
OKAY.

12:09.946 --> 12:12.470
[ CLATTERING ][ INHALES SHARPLY ]

12:12.514 --> 12:15.865
UH, LISBON, TAKE A LOOK
AT THIS.

12:15.909 --> 12:17.432
[ CHILDREN PLAYING
IN DISTANCE ]

12:17.475 --> 12:18.520
HI!

12:19.913 --> 12:22.306
MAYBE THERE WASN'T
ANYBODY THERE THAT DAY.

12:22.350 --> 12:23.873
MAYBE.

12:23.917 --> 12:25.788
WHAT WAS THE WEATHER LIKE
DAY OF THE MURDER?

12:25.832 --> 12:30.619
[ EXHALES ] CRIME REPORT
SAYS IT WAS...

12:30.662 --> 12:32.186
MID 70s, CLEAR SKIES.

12:32.229 --> 12:35.102
PERFECT DAY FOR THE PARK.
WHICH BEGS A QUESTION.

12:35.145 --> 12:37.887
WHY WOULD YOU BREAK IN
THROUGH THAT WINDOW

12:37.931 --> 12:41.238
WHEN YOU CAN BREAK IN
AROUND THE SIDE THROUGH THERE,

12:41.282 --> 12:43.850
HIDDEN FROM THE STREET?

12:43.893 --> 12:46.374
NOW THE BODY WAS FOUND HERE,

12:46.417 --> 12:48.768
WITH A HALF-FINISHED
CROSSWORD PUZZLE AND A PEN.

12:48.811 --> 12:51.814
SO WE CAN ASSUME THAT SHE WAS
SITTING...THERE.

12:55.252 --> 12:56.558
SHE WOULD HAVE HEARD HIM.

12:56.601 --> 12:58.865
YES, SHE WOULD HAVE
HEARD HIM.

12:58.908 --> 13:01.171
BUT IF RAYMOND
WAS THE KILLER...

13:01.215 --> 13:04.609
VERY EASY TO PUSH THAT SCREEN
OUT FROM THE INSIDE.

13:04.653 --> 13:06.786
YEAH, BUT THE TIME OF DEATH,
HE COULDN'T HAVE DONE IT.

13:06.829 --> 13:11.486
SURE.

13:11.529 --> 13:13.096
UH, LIVER TEMPERATURE, YES.

13:17.144 --> 13:20.669
SHE HAD A FAN
POINTED RIGHT AT HER,

13:20.712 --> 13:22.671
LIKE IT WAS REALLY HOT.

13:25.892 --> 13:27.328
BUT IT WAS MID 70s.

13:29.504 --> 13:33.029
PERFECT DAY, FAN...

13:33.073 --> 13:34.857
YOU EVER COOK A ROAST?

13:34.901 --> 13:36.206
OF COURSE.

13:36.250 --> 13:37.860
YEAH. SORRY.

13:37.904 --> 13:39.253
MY AUNT USED TO DO IT
THIS WAY --

13:39.296 --> 13:41.995
SHE TURNED THE OVEN
WAY UP HIGH.

13:42.038 --> 13:44.562
YOU HEAT IT,
YOU PUT THE ROAST IN,

13:44.606 --> 13:45.825
AND THEN YOU TURN IT OFF.

13:47.870 --> 13:51.134
SO MAYBE...

13:51.178 --> 13:54.355
HE TURNS THE THERMOSTAT
ALL THE WAY UP.

13:54.398 --> 13:56.966
[ CLICKING ]

13:57.010 --> 13:58.663
TELLS HER IT'S BROKEN.

13:58.707 --> 14:01.144
[ SPEAKING INAUDIBLY ]

14:01.188 --> 14:02.537
AND THEN HE TURNS
THE THERMOSTAT OFF

14:02.580 --> 14:04.626
AFTER HE KILLS HER.

14:04.669 --> 14:07.585
THE ROOM AND NICOLE
COOL OFF SLOWER,

14:07.629 --> 14:11.154
MAKING IT SEEM LIKE SHE DIED
LATER THAN SHE ACTUALLY DID.

14:11.198 --> 14:13.330
EXACTLY.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.637
WHAT ABOUT THE FAN?

14:15.680 --> 14:18.422
HE TURNED OFF BOTH THE FAN
AND THE THERMOSTAT.

14:18.466 --> 14:20.598
[ CLICKING ]

14:23.036 --> 14:25.038
AND THEN HE LEAVES.

14:25.081 --> 14:27.040
THEN HE LEAVES.

14:27.083 --> 14:28.258
UH --

14:28.302 --> 14:30.130
THE FRONT DOOR.

14:30.173 --> 14:33.307
LOOKS LIKE IT WAS
WIPED DOWN.FOR PRINTS.

14:33.350 --> 14:35.396
RAYMOND DOESN'T HAVE TO
WORRY ABOUT PRINTS.

14:35.439 --> 14:37.572
IT'S HIS HOUSE.WELL, MAYBE HE GOT
BLOOD ON IT.

14:37.615 --> 14:39.791
NO. HE'S TOO METICULOUS.

14:39.835 --> 14:43.404
YOU'RE RIGHT.

14:43.447 --> 14:46.755
MAYBE HE WAS WIPING OFF
SOMEBODY ELSE'S PRINTS.

14:46.798 --> 14:49.845
UH-HUH. OKAY. OKAY.

14:49.889 --> 14:51.325
A WOMAN.[ DOOR CLOSES ]

14:51.368 --> 14:53.980
IT HAD TO HAVE BEEN
A WOMAN.

14:54.023 --> 14:57.200
FOR THE RED LIGHT
PHOTOGRAPH.

14:57.244 --> 14:59.202
WE NEED TO FIND OUT WHO THAT
WOMAN WAS IN THE CAR.

14:59.246 --> 15:01.596
IT GIVES HIM MOTIVE.
HOW DO WE FIND HER?

15:01.639 --> 15:03.728
WELL, I THINK IT'S TIME
I PAID OUR PAL RAYMOND A VISIT,

15:03.772 --> 15:05.339
HAVE A LITTLE TALK ABOUT

15:05.382 --> 15:07.645
"TACTICAL SOLUTIONS
TO URBAN TERRORISM."

15:07.689 --> 15:09.212
I TOLD YOU.TOLD ME WHAT?

15:09.256 --> 15:11.562
YOU CAN'T QUIT.
YOU'RE HAVING TOO MUCH FUN.

15:11.606 --> 15:13.956
Judy: [ SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ][ Normal voice ] JUDY.

15:14.000 --> 15:16.350
OH!UH, I'M SORRY.

15:16.393 --> 15:17.786
UH, I THINK WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO PASS ON THIS ONE.

15:17.829 --> 15:20.571
NOT ENOUGH CLOSET SPACE.YOU HEARD THE WOMAN.

15:33.019 --> 15:34.324
YES?

15:35.325 --> 15:36.805
COLONEL RAYMOND.

15:36.848 --> 15:37.980
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

15:38.024 --> 15:40.809
THE F.B.I. CONSULTANT,
RIGHT?

15:40.852 --> 15:43.203
YOU HERE FOR THE SEMINAR?

15:43.246 --> 15:46.467
OH, THAT'S NO WAY TO LEARN.
I PREFER ONE-ON-ONE.

15:46.510 --> 15:48.425
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

15:48.469 --> 15:50.036
YOU NEED SOME ADVICE?

15:50.079 --> 15:51.472
OH, GIVEN THE WAY YOUR BOYS
PERFORMED

15:51.515 --> 15:53.169
IN THAT GAME YESTERDAY,
I THOUGHT

15:53.213 --> 15:55.084
YOU MIGHT BE ASKING
FOR ADVICE YOURSELF.

15:55.128 --> 15:58.131
[ CHUCKLES ] YOUR AGENTS
GOT LUCKY.

15:58.174 --> 16:00.046
NOW I TRY TO TEACH MY MEN
NOT TO LET THE OTHER SIDE

16:00.089 --> 16:01.612
GET LUCKY LIKE THAT.

16:01.656 --> 16:02.962
YEAH, I COULD HEAR YOUR MEN

16:03.005 --> 16:04.659
WHISPERING THEIR PLANS
BACK AND FORTH.

16:04.702 --> 16:07.053
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING
ABOUT PLANS, COLONEL.

16:07.096 --> 16:09.620
THEY GET IN THE WAY
OF INSTINCTS.

16:09.664 --> 16:11.318
YOU DON'T BELIEVE
IN BATTLE PLANS?

16:11.361 --> 16:13.189
WELL, WASN'T IT NAPOLEON
THAT ONCE SAID,

16:13.233 --> 16:15.670
"NO PLAN SURVIVES
THE FIRST SHOT"?

16:15.713 --> 16:18.325
A STUDENT OF COMBAT.

16:18.368 --> 16:19.848
MORE OF PEOPLE.

16:21.589 --> 16:23.504
WELL, NAPOLEON DID
ALL RIGHT IN HIS DAY,

16:23.547 --> 16:25.375
BUT I'D TELL HIM
THE SECRET TO THAT IS

16:25.419 --> 16:27.899
NEVER LET YOUR OPPONENT
FIRE THAT FIRST SHOT.

16:27.943 --> 16:32.643
THAT'S A LITTLE UNSPORTING.

16:32.687 --> 16:35.081
MAYBE THE ONLY REAL THING
WE HAVE LEFT.

16:35.124 --> 16:38.301
THAT'S THE STUPIDEST THING
I'VE EVER HEARD.

16:39.694 --> 16:41.304
YOU'RE TRYING TO PROVOKE ME.

16:41.348 --> 16:43.524
WHY?

16:43.567 --> 16:46.266
TO SEE HOW YOU REACT.

16:47.658 --> 16:50.052
DID YOU LEARN SOMETHING?

16:52.489 --> 16:54.013
YEAH.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.016
I THINK I DID.

16:57.059 --> 16:59.192
THANKS FOR YOUR TIME.

17:02.499 --> 17:04.893
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

17:06.112 --> 17:07.939
IT'S CALLED A RUNGU.

17:07.983 --> 17:10.725
IT'S A MASAI WARRIOR
WAR CLUB.

17:10.768 --> 17:12.640
IT'S NORMAL DECOR
FOR A SOLDIER.

17:12.683 --> 17:15.164
YES, BUT THE AFRICAN ART

17:15.208 --> 17:17.340
DOESN'T HAVE ANY ANALOG
IN THE CRIME SCENE PHOTOS.

17:17.384 --> 17:18.907
EXCUSE ME?

17:18.950 --> 17:20.430
WELL, EVERYTHING ELSE
IN THE OFFICE --

17:20.474 --> 17:22.737
THE BOOKS, THE PHOTOS,
THE PATRIOTIC ART --

17:22.780 --> 17:24.304
ALL HAD SOMETHING SIMILAR
IN THE HOUSE

17:24.347 --> 17:26.567
THE WAY IT WAS DECORATED
THE DAY OF THE MURDER.

17:26.610 --> 17:27.785
BUT THERE WAS
NO AFRICAN ART.

17:27.829 --> 17:30.049
NO.

17:30.092 --> 17:32.834
SO...MAYBE HE HAD
A GIRLFRIEND,

17:32.877 --> 17:35.793
AND MAYBE SHE HAD AN INTEREST
IN AFRICAN ART.HUH.

17:35.837 --> 17:38.100
SHOULD WE TAIL HIM?NO, HE'S A SOLDIER
IN MILITARY INTELLIGENCE.

17:38.144 --> 17:39.710
HE CAN SPOT A TAIL.

17:39.754 --> 17:42.061
MOST AFFAIRS ARE WITH
PEOPLE THAT YOU MEET

17:42.104 --> 17:43.453
IN YOUR EVERYDAY LIFE.

17:43.497 --> 17:45.368
THEY'RE FAMILIAR.
WORKPLACE.

17:45.412 --> 17:47.892
SO SHE'S A MARINE.

17:47.936 --> 17:49.981
[ SIGHS ] WELL,
THE WYNN COMPLEX HAS

17:50.025 --> 17:51.592
OVER A THOUSAND
GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES,

17:51.635 --> 17:53.855
EVERYTHING FROM THE N.S.A.
TO THE POST OFFICE.

17:53.898 --> 17:57.250
HOW DO WE NARROW THAT DOWN?

17:57.293 --> 17:58.729
PREFERABLY SOMEONE THAT
HASN'T BEEN INVOLVED

17:58.773 --> 18:00.166
IN THE TRAINING EXERCISES.

18:00.209 --> 18:02.342
THAT LEAVES OUT LISBON,
YOURSELF.

18:02.385 --> 18:03.952
I WAS THERE TUESDAY
FOR MILITARY TRAINING.

18:03.995 --> 18:06.128
HMM. OKAY. COULD YOU
DO ME A FAVOR?HMM?

18:06.172 --> 18:08.913
NEXT TIME WYLIE STEALS A GLANCE
AT YOU, COULD YOU WAVE HIM IN?

18:08.957 --> 18:10.959
WHAT?

18:12.961 --> 18:16.007
[ TELEPHONE RINGING
IN DISTANCE ]

18:22.449 --> 18:23.667
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:23.711 --> 18:26.148
[ BREATHES SHARPLY ]

18:26.192 --> 18:27.932
STOP IT.

18:27.976 --> 18:31.022
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:34.765 --> 18:36.289
HEY, I'M FROM I.T.

18:36.332 --> 18:37.986
WHAT CAN I HELP YOU WITH?WRONG OFFICE.

18:44.384 --> 18:45.994
ALL RIGHT. THANKS.

18:49.563 --> 18:51.130
HEY. FROM I.T.

18:51.173 --> 18:53.654
[ BLOWS AIR ]

18:53.697 --> 18:54.959
[ KNOCKS ]

18:57.962 --> 18:59.616
HI, I'M HERE FROM I.T.

18:59.660 --> 19:00.835
THANK YOU.

19:05.318 --> 19:06.493
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

19:06.536 --> 19:08.147
COME IN.

19:09.713 --> 19:12.020
HEY. I'M FROM I.T.

19:12.063 --> 19:14.022
[ CLICKS MOUSE ]

19:14.065 --> 19:16.155
IS THIS ABOUT CANDY PILOTS?

19:18.418 --> 19:19.854
'CAUSE I KNOW YOU'RE NOT
SUPPOSED TO DOWNLOAD GAMES.

19:19.897 --> 19:21.682
I JUST -- I HAVE
A LOT OF DOWN TIME.

19:22.639 --> 19:24.511
WHAT? NO.

19:24.554 --> 19:25.903
OH.

19:25.947 --> 19:28.297
OKAY THEN. WHAT'S UP?

19:28.341 --> 19:30.734
I'M HERE TO CHECK
YOUR DATA STACKS.

19:32.127 --> 19:33.998
WHAT'S A DATA STACK?

19:36.262 --> 19:37.437
HUH?

19:37.480 --> 19:39.221
I ASKED,
WHAT'S A DATA STACK?

19:39.265 --> 19:40.570
OH, RIGHT.

19:40.614 --> 19:42.920
HERE, I'LL SHOW YOU.

19:44.487 --> 19:46.968
DENISE SPARKS, 36.

19:47.011 --> 19:49.188
SHE WORKS AS AN INFORMATION
ANALYST FOR THE D.O.D.

19:49.231 --> 19:51.277
COULD SHE AND RAYMOND
HAVE CROSSED PATHS?

19:51.320 --> 19:53.148
SHE DOES A WEEKLY
ANTITERRORISM BRIEFING

19:53.192 --> 19:55.106
FOR TOP BRASS,
INCLUDING RAYMOND.

19:55.150 --> 19:57.979
LOVE SPRINGS UP
IN THE UNLIKELIEST OF PLACES.

19:58.022 --> 19:59.981
I FOUND HER FACEBOOK PAGE.

20:00.024 --> 20:01.896
SHE'S GOT LOTS OF PHOTOS
OF HER IN AFRICA.

20:01.939 --> 20:03.985
NO PICTURES OF HER
AND A BOYFRIEND.

20:04.028 --> 20:05.813
UH, COULD YOU PUT HER
NEXT TO THE RED LIGHT PHOTO?

20:05.856 --> 20:06.901
MM-HMM.

20:10.774 --> 20:13.212
THAT COULD BE HER.

20:13.255 --> 20:15.431
COULD YOU ENGINEER
A MEETING?

20:15.475 --> 20:17.694
GET A READ ON HER,
SEE IF SHE'S OUR GIRL?

20:17.738 --> 20:19.522
YEAH.WELL, WHY SHOULD I HAVE
ALL THE FUN?

20:19.566 --> 20:23.222
[ MACHINE WHIRS ]

20:25.354 --> 20:26.790
WHAT WAS SHE LIKE?

20:26.834 --> 20:28.227
I DON'T KNOW.
SHE SEEMED NICE.

20:28.270 --> 20:31.186
WE'RE JUST LOOKING
FOR IMPRESSIONS.

20:31.230 --> 20:33.797
SHE'S VERY CLEAN,
WELL PUT TOGETHER.

20:33.841 --> 20:35.234
MM-HMM.

20:35.277 --> 20:36.974
MANICURED HANDS.

20:37.018 --> 20:39.150
BUT SHE CHEWED THE SKIN
AROUND HER NAILS.

20:40.587 --> 20:42.110
WHAT DID SHE ORDER?

20:42.153 --> 20:44.199
COFFEE, BLACK.

20:44.243 --> 20:45.940
PAID CASH.

20:45.983 --> 20:48.682
SHE WAITED UNTIL THE WOMAN
BEHIND THE COUNTER

20:48.725 --> 20:50.553
COULD SEE HER PUT HER TIP
IN THE TIP JAR.

20:50.597 --> 20:54.078
INTERESTING.
I WONDER IF I DO THAT.

20:54.122 --> 20:56.429
FOUR SUGARS.
IT WAS A LOT.

20:56.472 --> 20:58.735
YEAH, THAT IS A LOT.
SO YOU TALKED TO HER.

20:58.779 --> 21:03.914
YOU SAID, "I LIKE YOUR BAG." HOW'D YOU KNOW THAT?

21:03.958 --> 21:05.742
WELL, IT WORKED.
WE TALKED.

21:05.786 --> 21:07.178
TELL ME ABOUT HER.

21:07.222 --> 21:08.963
I DON'T KNOW.
SHE'S RESERVED.

21:09.006 --> 21:11.052
IT'S THE KIND OF QUIET WHERE
MAYBE SHE COULD BE

21:11.095 --> 21:14.055
A RAGING BITCH,
OR SHE'S JUST SHY.

21:14.098 --> 21:16.753
AND WHAT'S YOUR VERDICT?

21:16.797 --> 21:18.320
YOU WANT ME TO SAY
IF SHE'S A KILLER

21:18.364 --> 21:19.756
BASED ON SPENDING
ONE MINUTE WITH HER?

21:19.800 --> 21:21.236
SURE.

21:21.280 --> 21:24.239
WELL, HOW DO I DO THAT?

21:24.283 --> 21:29.070
YOU JUST HAVE TO LISTEN
TO IT.

21:29.113 --> 21:31.246
1...2...

21:31.290 --> 21:32.856
THE ANSWER IS YES.
I DON'T NEED 3.

21:32.900 --> 21:34.249
SHE COULD HAVE DONE IT.

21:34.293 --> 21:35.990
EVERYTHING ABOUT HER,

21:36.033 --> 21:37.513
IT JUST SEEMED LIKE
SHE WAS WEARING A MASK.

21:37.557 --> 21:39.428
OKAY THEN.

21:39.472 --> 21:41.648
VERY NICE, AGENT LISBON.

21:41.691 --> 21:43.084
THANK YOU.

21:51.832 --> 21:53.355
[ FAINT GUNFIRE ]

21:53.399 --> 21:56.184
SO THE THEORY IS

21:56.227 --> 21:58.404
DENISE HELPED RAYMOND
KILL HIS WIFE,

21:58.447 --> 22:00.144
AND THEN SHE DRESSED UP
LIKE HIM?

22:00.188 --> 22:02.364
WELL, JANE THINKS THEY RAN
THE RED LIGHT ON PURPOSE.

22:02.408 --> 22:04.671
THE PHOTOGRAPH WOULD GIVE
RAYMOND AN AIRTIGHT ALIBI.

22:04.714 --> 22:06.847
CAN I SEE THAT?

22:06.890 --> 22:08.152
YEAH.

22:12.853 --> 22:14.637
DON'T DO IT FAST.
DO IT RIGHT.

22:17.597 --> 22:19.729
WE HAVE NOTHING
APPROACHING HARD EVIDENCE.

22:19.773 --> 22:21.252
YEAH, WELL, THAT'S
WHERE YOU COME IN.

22:23.690 --> 22:26.127
THIS IS WHERE THE RED LIGHT
PHOTO WAS TAKEN.

22:26.170 --> 22:28.434
THEY DUMPED THE CAR HERE,
WHERE JEFFERSON FOUND IT.

22:28.477 --> 22:30.436
IT'S WALKING DISTANCE
TO THE WYNN COMPLEX.

22:30.479 --> 22:31.785
THEY WALKED THERE
RIGHT AFTER THE MURDER?

22:31.828 --> 22:33.134
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
THE TIMING WORKS.

22:33.177 --> 22:34.831
DENISE...

22:34.875 --> 22:37.312
HAD TO CHANGE BACK INTO
HER WORK CLOTHES AT SOME POINT.

22:37.356 --> 22:39.445
NOTICE SHE'S NOT DRIVING.SO?

22:39.488 --> 22:41.229
JANE'S THEORY IS SHE
CHANGED CLOTHES IN THE CAR.

22:41.272 --> 22:43.274
THEN SHE HAD TO
THROW THEM AWAY.

22:43.318 --> 22:45.625
MAYBE SHE THREW THEM
OUT THE CAR WINDOW.

22:45.668 --> 22:48.497
OR SHE PULLED OVER AND THREW IT
AWAY IN A DUMPSTER.

22:48.541 --> 22:50.934
I DON'T THINK THEY RISK
GETTING OUT OF THE CAR.

22:50.978 --> 22:52.371
[ GUNFIRE CONTINUES ]

22:52.414 --> 22:53.981
EVEN IF JANE'S THEORY
IS RIGHT,

22:54.024 --> 22:56.113
THAT'S AT LEAST 5 MILES.

22:56.157 --> 22:57.767
I CAN'T SEARCH 5 MILES.

22:57.811 --> 22:59.247
YOU WON'T HAVE TO.

23:01.902 --> 23:03.425
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:24.011 --> 23:25.404
GO.

23:33.586 --> 23:35.457
DON'T RUSH.

23:35.501 --> 23:37.764
I-I MEAN, SHE WOULDN'T
HAVE RUSHED.

23:37.807 --> 23:40.767
AND WE WANT IT
TO TIME OUT RIGHT.

23:40.810 --> 23:42.246
SURE.

23:56.260 --> 23:57.566
DONE.

24:01.875 --> 24:03.354
[ SEAT BELTS CLICK ]

24:08.751 --> 24:10.840
OKAY, SO NOW WHAT?

24:10.884 --> 24:13.277
WE GRID SEARCH.

24:13.321 --> 24:16.106
DIVIDE THE SIDE OF THE STREET
INTO 1-FOOT SQUARES.

24:16.150 --> 24:18.544
EXAMINE EVERY SQUARE
CAREFULLY.

24:18.587 --> 24:21.590
THAT'S GONNA TAKE
A LONG TIME.

24:21.634 --> 24:23.287
KEEP TALKING, IT'LL TAKE
EVEN LONGER.

24:23.331 --> 24:25.420
YOU HEARD NORTH, I HEAD SOUTH.

24:28.554 --> 24:31.426
[ VEHICLES PASSING OVERHEAD ]

25:09.682 --> 25:12.162
HELLO?

25:12.206 --> 25:14.034
HELLO?!

25:14.077 --> 25:15.905
F.B.I. ANYONE HOME?

25:50.984 --> 25:53.334
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

25:54.465 --> 25:56.206
VEGA?

25:56.250 --> 25:58.078
I THINK I'VE GOT SOMETHING.

26:07.043 --> 26:10.351
[ MOUSE CLICKING ]

26:16.444 --> 26:18.228
AGENT LISBON.

26:18.272 --> 26:19.621
MAY I HAVE A MOMENT
OF YOUR TIME?

26:19.665 --> 26:21.405
SURE. HAVE A SEAT.

26:21.449 --> 26:23.538
SOMEPLACE PRIVATE.

26:38.640 --> 26:40.163
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

26:40.207 --> 26:43.645
I JUST WANTED TO KNOW IF YOU
THINK I MURDERED MY WIFE.

26:45.647 --> 26:48.519
WELL, I CERTAINLY
THINK YOU DID. HI.

26:48.563 --> 26:51.740
THEN ARREST ME.

26:54.438 --> 26:57.137
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

26:57.180 --> 26:58.573
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE?

26:58.617 --> 26:59.922
JUST GOT AMBUSHED.

26:59.966 --> 27:01.924
A DETECTIVE RIOS CALLED ME.

27:01.968 --> 27:03.926
HE WANTED TO KNOW IF THE F.B.I.
HAD BEEN TOUCH

27:03.970 --> 27:05.711
ABOUT A CIVIL RIGHTS CASE.

27:05.754 --> 27:08.278
DO YOU KNOW ANYTHING ABOUT
THIS LITTLE INVESTIGATION?

27:13.283 --> 27:15.677
WELL, THAT'S A DAMN SHAME.
I LIKED YOU.

27:15.721 --> 27:18.245
THE INVESTIGATION ENDS NOW.

27:18.288 --> 27:20.682
THANK YOU.

27:20.726 --> 27:22.728
YOU SEEM LIKE A SMART PERSON.

27:22.771 --> 27:24.643
KNOW WHEN YOU'VE
OVERPLAYED YOUR HAND.

27:29.430 --> 27:31.693
MY OFFICE. NOW.

27:37.003 --> 27:39.309
WE'VE GOT THE FABRIC
AT THE LAB RIGHT NOW, RUSH JOB.

27:39.353 --> 27:41.921
IF IT HOLDS EITHER DENISE
OR RAYMOND'S D.N.A.

27:41.964 --> 27:43.444
OR SOME OF NICOLE'S BLOOD,

27:43.487 --> 27:45.141
I THINK WE'VE GOT
A REAL SHOT AT THIS.

27:45.185 --> 27:49.842
A PIECE OF FABRIC
FROM A HOMELESS ENCAMPMENT.

27:49.885 --> 27:52.975
EVEN IF THE LAB
TURNS UP ANYTHING,

27:53.019 --> 27:54.890
YOU DON'T HAVE IT.

27:54.934 --> 27:59.939
NOW I THINK THAT YOU AND JANE
DID SOME NICE WORK,

27:59.982 --> 28:02.376
BUT NOT ENOUGH
TO REOPEN THE CASE.

28:02.419 --> 28:04.378
NO PROSECUTOR IS GONNA
GO AFTER THIS MAN

28:04.421 --> 28:06.162
WITHOUT HAVING SOLID EVIDENCE.

28:06.206 --> 28:09.470
WE'VE GOTTEN AS CLOSE AS WE CAN
WORKING OFF THE BOOKS.

28:09.513 --> 28:11.777
UH -- MAYBE IF YOU PUT US
IN FRONT OF A JUDGE.

28:11.820 --> 28:13.343
ANYTHING SHORT OF A CONFESSION,

28:13.387 --> 28:15.911
AND THEY WILL NEVER REOPEN
THE CASE.

28:15.955 --> 28:19.219
I'M SORRY. IT'S OVER.

28:23.876 --> 28:26.487
WHEN WE GET THE RESULTS
FROM THE LAB,

28:26.530 --> 28:29.011
WE'LL JUST TRY AGAIN.Jane: HMM.

28:29.055 --> 28:32.014
ANYTHING
SHORT OF A CONFESSION.

28:32.058 --> 28:33.189
WHAT?

28:35.496 --> 28:37.585
[ Whispers ]
LET'S GO FOR THE CONFESSION.

29:19.540 --> 29:21.498
[ CLICKS TONGUE ] HEY.

29:21.542 --> 29:23.762
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

29:23.805 --> 29:25.764
WELL, I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.

29:25.807 --> 29:27.722
I DIDN'T SEND YOU A MESSAGE.

29:27.766 --> 29:30.681
[ BUZZER ]

29:30.725 --> 29:33.336
MORNING. UH, COULD YOU
HAVE A SEAT, PLEASE?

29:33.380 --> 29:35.774
I'M SORRY. PATRICK JANE,
TERESA LISBON.

29:40.909 --> 29:43.346
HE DIDN'T TELL YOU
WE'RE INVESTIGATING YOU?

29:46.436 --> 29:48.395
THIS IS OUTRAGEOUS.

29:48.438 --> 29:49.831
I'M CALLING ABBOTT.

29:49.875 --> 29:51.224
OH, FEEL FREE.

29:52.486 --> 29:55.924
[ TOUCH SCREEN CLICKING ]

29:58.666 --> 30:01.364
[ PHONE VIBRATING, RINGING ]HEH. OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

30:01.408 --> 30:04.628
THAT'S EMBARRASSING. GUESS
I PICKED UP THE WRONG PHONE.

30:04.672 --> 30:07.066
YOU'LL HAVE TO TALK TO HIM
LATER.

30:07.109 --> 30:09.416
THEN I WANT MY LAWYER HERE.

30:09.459 --> 30:11.113
YOU'LL BE TALKING
TO YOUR LAWYER SOON ENOUGH.

30:11.157 --> 30:15.030
[ SIGHS SHARPLY ]
WE'LL GET TO THAT.

30:15.074 --> 30:18.077
[ EXHALES ] YOU WANT TO TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON?

30:18.120 --> 30:21.907
YES. IN THIS BRIEFCASE, I HAVE
A REPORT FROM THE CRIME LAB.

30:21.950 --> 30:23.778
I SENT SOMETHING IN
TO BE TESTED.

30:23.822 --> 30:26.128
WHEN WE OPEN IT, WE WILL KNOW
IF IT IMPLICATES

30:26.172 --> 30:27.869
ONE OF YOU, OR BOTH OF YOU.

30:27.913 --> 30:31.481
IF ONE OF YOU CONFESSES
BEFORE I OPEN THE BRIEFCASE,

30:31.525 --> 30:33.614
WE'LL CUT YOU A DEAL.

30:33.657 --> 30:35.616
AFTER THE BRIEFCASE
IS OPEN,

30:35.659 --> 30:37.531
NO DEALS FOR ANYONE.

30:37.574 --> 30:41.230
I'M GONNA OPEN THE BRIEFCASE
IN FIVE MINUTES.

30:42.623 --> 30:44.843
AND THAT FIVE MINUTES...

30:46.540 --> 30:48.020
STARTS NOW.

31:09.171 --> 31:10.694
YOU DON'T HAVE ANYTHING
ON US.

31:10.738 --> 31:13.436
WELL, WE'LL SOON SEE,
WON'T WE?

31:13.480 --> 31:16.048
[ Whispers ] SO EXCITING.

31:17.310 --> 31:19.399
I'M WALKING OUT OF HERE.

31:19.442 --> 31:20.400
GO.

31:21.923 --> 31:23.533
WE SHOULD GO.

31:23.577 --> 31:33.630
YOU SHOULD STAY.

31:33.630 --> 31:47.383
YOU SHOULD STAY.

31:47.427 --> 31:49.820
[ SIGHS ]

31:52.867 --> 31:54.303
WE'LL SIT HERE
FOR FIVE MINUTES,

31:54.347 --> 31:55.914
LET THEM
OPEN THE BRIEFCASE,

31:55.957 --> 31:57.350
SEE THAT THEY DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING ON US,

31:57.393 --> 31:58.917
AND THEN WE WALK
OUT OF HERE.

31:58.960 --> 32:00.353
AARON --NOT A WORD.

32:00.396 --> 32:02.137
DEFINITELY
IN A RELATIONSHIP.YEP.

32:02.181 --> 32:04.748
THAT'S NOT A CRIME.

32:04.792 --> 32:06.620
THERE'S NO NEED --NO -- I LOVE HIM.

32:09.014 --> 32:11.755
[ Lowered voice ]
I LOVE YOU.

32:11.799 --> 32:13.105
BUT NOW'S NOT THE TIME.

32:13.148 --> 32:14.976
BUT YOU KNOW
THAT I WOULD NEVER --

32:15.020 --> 32:16.412
OF COURSE.

32:16.456 --> 32:18.240
AND YOU KNOW.

32:27.510 --> 32:30.774
IF EITHER OF YOU WAS SMART,
THIS GAME WOULD BE OVER BY NOW.

32:33.255 --> 32:35.127
DO YOU EVER LAY AWAKE
AT NIGHT WONDERING

32:35.170 --> 32:37.303
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO YOU
WHEN HE GETS TIRED OF YOU,

32:37.346 --> 32:39.348
JUST LIKE HE GOT TIRED
OF NICOLE?

32:42.177 --> 32:45.180
COLONEL, YOU'VE CARRIED OUT
BATTLE PLANS BEFORE.

32:45.224 --> 32:47.748
HOW HARD COULD
THE PERFECT MURDER BE?

32:47.791 --> 32:49.010
YOU DID A NICE JOB.

32:49.054 --> 32:51.056
VERY NICE.
ONE LITTLE MISTAKE.

32:51.099 --> 32:53.014
WAS IT THE THERMOSTAT?

32:53.058 --> 32:54.755
OR THE WIG.

32:54.798 --> 32:57.497
OR WAS IT THE CLOTHES
YOU THREW OUT THE WINDOW

32:57.540 --> 32:58.977
ON -- WHERE WAS IT?

32:59.020 --> 33:00.674
23rd STREET.23rd STREET.

33:00.717 --> 33:04.199
HMM.

33:04.243 --> 33:07.115
TIME WAITS FOR NO MAN...
OR WOMAN.

33:12.642 --> 33:13.513
[ Normal voice ] THIS IS --[ Normal voice ] STOP TALKING.

33:13.556 --> 33:15.254
BUT, AARON --

33:15.297 --> 33:16.777
[ Lowered voice ]
WOMAN, I'M TELLING YOU.

33:19.345 --> 33:20.737
WHAT IS IT
YOU WANT TO SAY?

33:20.781 --> 33:23.436
[ EXHALES, SWALLOWS ]

33:23.479 --> 33:25.133
[ Whispers ] AARON...

33:25.177 --> 33:26.439
[ Loudly ]
DON'T BE STUPID!

33:26.482 --> 33:28.223
MMM.

33:35.926 --> 33:37.667
[ EXHALES ]

33:37.711 --> 33:38.973
[ STAMMERS ]

33:43.891 --> 33:45.110
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

33:45.153 --> 33:46.285
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TALK.

33:46.328 --> 33:48.069
WE DID IT.

33:48.113 --> 33:50.419
[ GASPS ] NO, YOUDID IT!

33:50.463 --> 33:52.813
NO, HE'S THE ONE WHO DID IT!
I DIDN'T DO IT! HE DID IT!

33:52.856 --> 33:54.162
YOU...

33:55.685 --> 33:57.600
[ SIGHS ]

33:57.644 --> 34:00.821
[ TELEPHONE RINGS
IN DISTANCE ]

34:00.864 --> 34:02.518
NICOLE SAID SHE'D
FIGHT THE DIVORCE.

34:02.562 --> 34:04.825
SHE'D TAKE THE HOUSE,
EVERYTHING.

34:08.785 --> 34:10.787
WHAT RIGHT DID SHE HAVE?

34:15.270 --> 34:19.274
U-UP UNTIL THE MOMENT
SHE DID IT,

34:19.318 --> 34:20.667
I DIDN'T THINK
IT WOULD HAPPEN.

34:26.455 --> 34:30.198
HE SAID IT WOULD BE
ONE BAD DAY,

34:30.242 --> 34:32.896
AND THEN A LIFETIME
OF HAPPINESS.

34:35.508 --> 34:37.640
[ BREATHS UNEVENLY ]
H-HE TOLD ME

34:37.684 --> 34:40.991
THAT SHE WOULD DRAG US BOTH
THROUGH THE MUD,

34:41.035 --> 34:44.778
THAT I'D BE LABELED
A HOME WRECKER.

34:55.745 --> 34:57.921
SHE SAID IT'D BE QUICK.

34:57.965 --> 34:59.314
[ EXHALES ]

35:08.280 --> 35:10.238
SHE WAS A DIFFERENT PERSON.

35:23.164 --> 35:25.688
[ BREATHS UNEVENLY ]

35:25.732 --> 35:26.733
HE LET ME IN.

35:31.955 --> 35:35.568
IT WAS SO HOT.

35:35.611 --> 35:38.875
AND WHEN HE LET ME IN, HE GOT
THE KNIFE OFF THE RACK.

35:41.008 --> 35:44.620
HE SMILED WHEN HE DID IT.

35:52.715 --> 35:55.196
HE ST--

35:55.240 --> 35:56.589
HE STABBED HER.

36:01.942 --> 36:05.163
[ FAN WHIRRING ]

36:17.305 --> 36:20.265
HE SAID SOMETHING
UNDER HIS BREATH WHEN --

36:20.308 --> 36:22.136
WHEN HE KILLED HER.

36:22.180 --> 36:24.660
[ SPEAKING INAUDIBLY ]

36:24.704 --> 36:26.662
I DON'T KNOW WHAT.

36:32.886 --> 36:35.018
HE STABBED HER.

36:36.933 --> 36:38.848
I JUST --

36:38.892 --> 36:40.459
JUST STOOD THERE...

36:44.419 --> 36:45.899
[ Voice breaks ]
AND WATCHED.

36:53.602 --> 36:55.604
SHE WASN'T THE SAME PERSON.

37:24.633 --> 37:27.114
CALL ZACH JEFFERSON'S ATTORNEY.
GIVE HER THE GOOD NEWS.

37:27.157 --> 37:28.202
GOT IT.

37:28.246 --> 37:30.465
JANE, WHICH ONE WAS IT?

37:30.509 --> 37:32.424
UH, WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

37:32.467 --> 37:34.730
WHO STABBED NICOLE?
WAS IT RAYMOND OR DENISE?

37:34.774 --> 37:36.166
I DON'T KNOW.

37:36.210 --> 37:37.429
YOU DON'T KNOW?

37:37.472 --> 37:39.387
NO. DOES IT MATTER?

37:39.431 --> 37:43.043
W-WELL, W-WHAT...
WELL, WHAT'S IN THAT?

37:43.086 --> 37:44.827
DID YOU REALLY GET EVIDENCE
ON ONE OF THEM?

37:44.871 --> 37:46.351
WHICH ONE WAS IT?GOOD NIGHT.

37:49.789 --> 37:52.705
ARE YOU AT ALL CURIOUS ABOUT
WHAT'S IN THAT BRIEFCASE?

37:52.748 --> 37:55.142
HAVEN'T STOPPED THINKING
ABOUT IT FOR A SECOND.

37:55.185 --> 37:57.536
SHOULD WE TAKE A LOOK?

37:57.579 --> 37:59.015
AH, I DON'T KNOW.

37:59.059 --> 38:01.061
COME ON, LET'S TAKE A LOOK.

38:01.104 --> 38:02.845
OKAY.

38:08.764 --> 38:10.113
[ LATCH CLICKS ]

38:14.074 --> 38:15.771
Jane: MEOW!

38:17.077 --> 38:19.384
[ CHUCKLING ] SORRY?

38:19.427 --> 38:21.516
Lisbon: OKAY. ADMIT IT.

38:21.560 --> 38:22.735
ADMIT WHAT?

38:22.778 --> 38:24.519
YOU ENJOYED YOURSELF.

38:24.563 --> 38:26.608
YOU LOVE THIS JOB
AS MUCH AS I DO.

38:26.652 --> 38:28.306
WELL, I LOVE EGGS,
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN

38:28.349 --> 38:30.743
I WANNA EAT NOTHING BUT OMELETS
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

38:30.786 --> 38:34.050
FAIR ENOUGH.
WHAT WAS THE ALTERNATIVE?

38:34.094 --> 38:35.791
WHAT'S THE ALTERNATIVE FOR US?

38:35.835 --> 38:37.793
YOU TALK ABOUT QUITTING,
BUT WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

38:37.837 --> 38:40.361
WHAT'S THE PLAN?WELL, I DON'T HAVE ONE
AS YET.

38:40.405 --> 38:44.844
WELL, THAT'S A PROBLEM,
ISN'T IT?

38:44.887 --> 38:46.454
MAYBE WE JUST NEED TO QUIT
AND SIT STILL FOR A WHILE.

38:46.498 --> 38:48.587
LET LIFE HAPPEN.

38:48.630 --> 38:51.198
LET A PLAN TAKE SEED.

38:51.241 --> 38:53.635
WAIT FOR PLAN SEEDS TO GROW?
WE'D DRIVE EACH OTHER CRAZY.

38:53.679 --> 38:56.682
MAYBE. MAYBE NOT.
MAYBE WE'D BE VERY HAPPY.

38:56.725 --> 38:58.118
WON'T KNOW UNTIL WE TRY.

38:58.161 --> 38:59.380
AREN'T YOU HAPPY NOW?

38:59.424 --> 39:01.339
WELL, I AM HAPPY
FOR THE FIRST TIME

39:01.382 --> 39:04.342
IN YOU KNOW HOW LONG,
BUT I'M SCARED.

39:04.385 --> 39:06.953
JANE, ONE OF US COULD GET
RUN OVER BY A BUS TOMORROW.

39:06.996 --> 39:08.650
NOT IF WE'RE ON A BEACH
IN POLYNESIA.

39:08.694 --> 39:09.869
BUSES CAN'T GO ON SAND.

39:09.912 --> 39:11.131
YOU COULD GET EATEN
BY A SHARK.

39:11.174 --> 39:14.221
NOT IF YOU DON'T GO
IN THE WATER.

39:14.264 --> 39:17.442
YEAH, THEY HAVE PALM TREES
AND HAMMOCKS AND COCKTAILS

39:17.485 --> 39:20.053
AND SUNSETS, PINEAPPLES...

39:20.096 --> 39:22.969
AND ENDLESS BOREDOM, SUNBURN,
BUGS THE SIZE OF HELICOPTERS.

39:23.012 --> 39:25.885
I'VE BEEN ON VACATION.

39:25.928 --> 39:27.669
IT WAS AN EXAMPLE
OF WE COULD AVOID BUSES.[ PEN SCRATCHING ]

39:27.713 --> 39:30.846
BUT WE COULD DO
ANYTHING WE WANT.

39:30.890 --> 39:32.587
WE COULD LEARN TO SAIL, BUY
A BOAT, SAIL AROUND THE WORLD.

39:32.631 --> 39:34.023
[ LAUGHS ] YEAH, RIGHT.

39:34.067 --> 39:36.678
W-WHAT? I ALWAYS WANTED
TO DO THAT.

39:36.722 --> 39:38.071
A LOT OF PEOPLE DO IT.

39:38.114 --> 39:40.116
I MEAN, WECOULD DO IT.

39:40.160 --> 39:43.381
AS IN WHALES AND STORMS
AND PIRATES? SCURVY?

39:43.424 --> 39:44.686
AND BESIDES, I GET SEASICK.

39:44.730 --> 39:46.253
YOU DO?YEAH.

39:46.296 --> 39:47.428
HOW BADLY?

39:47.472 --> 39:48.647
PRETTY BAD.OH.

39:48.690 --> 39:50.083
MAYBE YOU'D GET OVER THAT.

39:50.126 --> 39:52.259
WE ARE NOT
SAILING AROUND THE WORLD.

39:52.302 --> 39:53.565
ALL RIGHT.

39:53.608 --> 39:55.480
BEEKEEPING?
WHO DOESN'T LIKE HONEY?

39:55.523 --> 39:58.178
OH, YOU JUST COME UP WITH
THE BEST IDEAS. BEEKEEPING?

39:58.221 --> 39:59.571
WELL, I THINK YOU'D LOOK
VERY CUTE

39:59.614 --> 40:01.268
IN ONE OF THOSE LITTLE
BEEKEEPING SUITS.

40:01.311 --> 40:04.793
HOW IS THAT ROMANTIC?
[ SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY ]

40:04.837 --> 40:06.273
YEAH?
